The method should return an integer value representing the minimum possible score of a path between cities 1 and `n`.
The returned score should be the minimum score among all possible paths between cities 1 and `n`.
The score of a path is determined by the sum of the scores of all roads in that path.
The score of a road is determined by the absolute difference between the two cities connected by that road.
The returned score should be non-negative.
